    "full_draft": "The night before your daughter's wedding, on the terrace at Torrey Pines with the ocean behind you and the last light fading over the golf course, the music needs to feel inevitable, like it was always going to be there.\n\nChoosing live Spanish guitar for this particular evening says something about you: you know the difference between music that fills silence and music that actually holds a room.\n\nHere's the version of this that goes wrong: a guitarist who shows up, sets a volume, and plays through the entire evening at the same level whether the room is quiet or buzzing. The toasts happen over him. Someone has to walk over and ask him to turn down. That's not what this night deserves. What I do is read the room in real time, drop into the background when conversation picks up, let the guitar come forward in the quieter moments, and pause completely when someone stands up to speak.\n\nThe Lodge's terrace is one of the most naturally beautiful settings in San Diego. I'm fully self-contained, so there's no dependency on house power or venue infrastructure. That also means we're flexible if the evening flows indoors as the night cools.\n\nFor 3 hours of solo Spanish and classical guitar:\n\nSolo Classical/Spanish Guitar — 3 hours: $1,200\nIncludes professional sound, full setup and breakdown, and real-time calibration for the space.\n\nI can hold May 17 while you finalize things on your end. Just reply here or call me directly.\n\nAlex Guillen\n(619) 755-3246",
